definition: take-out (fast food)/(outer part of) tire/as well/besides/into the bargain/outer zone
band/belt/girdle/ribbon/tire/area/zone/region/CL:條|条[tiao2]/to wear/to carry/to take along/to bear (i.e. to have)/to lead/to bring/to look after/to raise

sentences.english: Maruko: To go. Would you give me some ketchup?
sentences.chinese: 外带。可以给我一些蕃茄酱吗？

sentences.english: The house has a diamond-shaped lawn with it.
sentences.chinese: 这幢房子外带一块菱形草坪。

sentences.english: We only have spring rolls today for take-out .
sentences.chinese: 今天我们的外带食物只有春卷。

sentences.english: Subpleural nodules are visible peripherally and in relation to the major fissures.
sentences.chinese: 可见肺外带胸膜下结节，与肺裂相关。

sentences.english: HRCT shows ill defined nodular areas of ground-glass opacity in the lung periphery.
sentences.chinese: HRCT显示肺外带边界不清的结节形毛玻璃样阴影。

sentences.english: A fine but irregular reticular pattern is present in the lung periphery, representing intralobular interstitial thickening.
sentences.chinese: 肺外带可见明显的不规则网状影，提示小叶间质增厚。

sentences.english: Tony always buys a takeout milk tea on his way home every day.
sentences.chinese: 汤尼每天回家的路上都会外带一杯奶茶。

sentences.english: I'd like to have a two-item combo to go, please.
sentences.chinese: 我想要外带一个二道菜的套餐。

sentences.english: He now has to live rent-free in a three-bedroom villa, complete with pool.
sentences.chinese: 他现住在一个免房租的三卧室别墅，外带游泳池。

sentences.english: Uh, can we have three chocolate mousses to go please?
sentences.chinese: 恩，能给我们三份巧克力慕思外带吗？

sentences.english: The hallway smelt of boiled cabbage and old rag mats.
sentences.chinese: 门厅里一股子清煮白菜外带破草垫的味儿。

sentences.english: That comes with a soup or salad. Which one would you like?
sentences.chinese: 这道菜外带一碗汤或者一份色拉。您想选哪一个？

sentences.english: You can buy coffee today in several different sizes of takeout containers.
sentences.chinese: 现在你可以用外带的容器买各种容量的咖啡。

sentences.english: One man ordered a rum and Coke to go.
sentences.chinese: 一个男人甚至点了一杯琴酒与可乐外带。

sentences.english: Just get a to-go box. Problem solved.
sentences.chinese: 就弄个外带盒子就好了，问题解决啦。

sentences.english: We don't need to buy take-out. I packed homemade lunches for us already.
sentences.chinese: 我们不用买外带食物，我已经带了在家做好的午餐了。

convenient/handy/easy/bento (a meal in a partitioned box)/lunchbox

(do sth) in passing/incidentally (while doing sth else)
full to the point of bursting/(coll.) at most
